text.section:
An instrument of writing is not subject to transfer tax to the same extent that it is not subject to recordation tax under:
§ 12-108(a) of this article (Transfer to government or public agency);
§ 12-108(c) of this article (Transfer between relatives and domestic partners);
§ 12-108(d) of this article (Transfer between spouses and domestic partners);
§ 12-108(e) of this article (Supplemental instrument);
§ 12-108(f) of this article (Previously recorded instrument);
§ 12-108(l) of this article (Judgments);
§ 12-108(n) of this article (Order of satisfaction);
§ 12-108(o) of this article (Participation agreement);
§ 12-108(p) of this article (Transfer of corporate property between related corporations);
§ 12-108(q) of this article (Corporate or partnership conveyance);
§ 12-108(r) of this article (Land installment contracts);
§ 12-108(s) of this article (Options to purchase real property);
§ 12-108(t) of this article (Deed for prior contract of sale);
§ 12-108(u) of this article (Leases of 7 years or less);
§ 12-108(v) of this article (Mergers);
§ 12-108(w) of this article (Consolidations);
§ 12-108(x) of this article (Cooperative housing corporations);
§ 12-108(y) or (bb) of this article (Transfer from predecessor entity or real estate enterprise to limited liability company);
§ 12-108(z) of this article (Transfer from a Class I Railroad Carrier to its wholly-owned limited liability company);
§ 12-108(aa) of this article (Transfers involving certain Maryland Stadium Authority affiliates);
§ 12-108(cc) of this article (Certain transfers to land trusts);
§ 12-108(dd) of this article (Transfer from an estate); or
§ 12-108(ee) of this article (Transfer to a trust and transfer from a trust under specified circumstances).

section.section:
An instrument of writing that transfers agricultural land that the transferee is acquiring for the purpose of maintaining the character of the land as agricultural land is not subject to the transfer tax, if the transferee:
is exempt from federal income tax under § 501(c)(3) of the Internal Revenue Code;
is incorporated, qualified, or registered to do business in the State;
has as its principal purpose the preservation of agricultural land, including the temporary ownership of an interest in land for the purpose of preserving the character of the land as agricultural land; and
has been certified by the Department as meeting the requirements of this paragraph.
